<div id="what" class="site-wrapper">
	<div class="site-wrapper-inner">
		<div class="container">
			<h1>
				Εxodus is a privacy auditing platform for Android applications.
			</h1>
			<h2>
				It detects behaviors which can be dangerous for user privacy like<br>
				ads, tracking, analytics, …
			</h2>
			<hr/>

			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-7">
					<h2>
						Comprehensive reports
					</h2>
					<p class="lead">
						Exodus provides a report for each analyzed application.
						Reports show the list of detected trackers, permissions
						and suspicious network traffic.
						Exodus also offers a brief description of each tracker
						is able to detect.
						<br>
						<br>
						<a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="https://reports.exodus-privacy.eu.org/">Browse reports</a>
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-5">
					<%= image_tag 'report.png', class: 'featurette-image img-fluid mx-auto' %>
				</div>
			</div>

			<hr/>

			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-5 order-md-1">
					<%= image_tag 'trackers.png', class: 'featurette-image img-fluid mx-auto' %>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-7 order-md-2">
					<h2>
						Static analysis
					</h2>
					<p class="lead">
						Exodus is able to detect presence of tracker code
						directly in the APK file without requiring decompilation.
						Exodus bases its analysis on APK files downloaded from
						Google Play.
						It ensures that Exodus analyzes applications which are
						available for any other user.
						<br>
						<br>
						<a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="https://reports.exodus-privacy.eu.org/">Browse reports</a>
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<hr/>

			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-7">
					<h2>
						Network analysis
					</h2>
					<p class="lead">
						Exodus executes the application and then dumps the
						entire network traffic generated by the simulated
						Android device.
						Exodus analyzes DNS, UDP, HTTP and HTTPS traffic to
						determine the collected data and the destination server.
						<br>
						<br>
						<a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="https://reports.exodus-privacy.eu.org/">Browse reports</a>
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-5">
					<%= image_tag 'network.png', class: 'featurette-image img-fluid mx-auto' %>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

